  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (d369d24 2023-07-02T00:05:10.773939000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test --match-test x -vvvv --fork-url https://rpc.flashbots.net --debug x\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n```\r\n[â ’] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\n2023-07-02T12:51:32.303362Z ERROR forge::runner: setUp failed reason=\"EvmError: Revert\" contract=0x7fa9385be102ac3eac297483dd6233d62b3e1496\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  Cannot start a runtime from within a runtime. This happens because a function (like `block_on`) attempted to block the current thread while the thread is being used to drive asynchronous tasks.\r\nLocation: /Users/runner/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-6f17d22bba15001f/tokio-1.28.2/src/runtime/scheduler/multi_thread/mod.rs:65\r\n\r\nThis is a bug. Consider reporting it at https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhenever i run `--debug x` on my test it gives me this error message.",
