    "body": "Hey @mattsse \r\nI get a similar error when running my test suite since today, using `forge 0.2.0 (9aefa43 2023-07-03T00:07:40.921128000Z)`. The exact error is \r\n\r\n`2023-07-03T14:19:08.920071Z ERROR forge::runner: setUp failed reason=\"82314932:\" contract=0x7fa9385be102ac3eac297483dd6233d62b3e1496`\r\n\r\nI found out that a code snipped in my contracts triggers this error:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n        if (!checkIfAddressIsWhitelisted(_from)) {\r\n            revert TransferModule__AddressIsNotWhitelisted(_from);\r\n        } else if (!checkIfAddressIsWhitelisted(_to)) {\r\n            revert TransferModule__AddressIsNotWhitelisted(_to);\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the ```!``` is removed the tests run successfully ðŸ¤”\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n        if (checkIfAddressIsWhitelisted(_from)) {\r\n            revert TransferModule__AddressIsNotWhitelisted(_from);\r\n        } else if (checkIfAddressIsWhitelisted(_to)) {\r\n            revert TransferModule__AddressIsNotWhitelisted(_to);\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n\r\nFull Code:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n    function checkTransferability(address _from, address _to) public view {\r\n        if (!checkIfAddressIsWhitelisted(_from)) {\r\n            revert TransferModule__AddressIsNotWhitelisted(_from);\r\n        } else if (!checkIfAddressIsWhitelisted(_to)) {\r\n            revert TransferModule__AddressIsNotWhitelisted(_to);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function checkIfAddressIsWhitelisted(address _address) public view returns (bool) {\r\n        return s_whitelist[_address];\r\n    }\r\n```    ",
